Summarise a waas object

Source: R/summary.waas.R
summary.waas.Rd

Summary the waas object in two ways. By default, the results are shown in the R console. The results can also be exported to the directory.

# S3 method for waas
summary(object, export = FALSE, file.name = NULL,
  digits = 4, ...)

Arguments

object

The waas object
export

A logical argument. If TRUE, a *.txt file is exported to the working directory
file.name

The name of the file if export = TRUE
digits

The significant digits to be shown.
...

Other arguments of the function

Examples


library(metan)
model = waas(data_ge,
             resp = c(GY, HM),
             gen = GEN,
             env = ENV,
             rep = REP)
#> Evaluating variable GY 50 % 
#> Evaluating variable HM 100 % 
#> Done!
